id: pm-xwah
title: Derive ALL MCP tool inputSchemas from *_FLAG_CONTRACTS — eliminate hand-declared parallel schema tables (extend the pm_copy pattern)
description: "Class fix behind pm-zx13 (schema/flag drift, closed) and pm-hno5 (pm_copy nested-options drift, closed via PR#545). Today only pm_copy imports COPY_FLAG_CONTRACTS; the other ~27 tools hand-declare schemas that the pm-4os2 golden file can only catch AFTER drift ships. Generating schemas from the single flag-contract source makes CLI/MCP input parity structural. Duplicate check: pm-srns owns OUTPUT envelope grammar; pm-0z7n owns CLI alias sweep; pm-9k90 owns tool TIERING; none owns input-schema derivation. Sequence freely; no blockers."
