acceptance_criteria: "Every mutation/query MCP tool in src/mcp/tool-definitions.ts derives its flat camelCase inputSchema keys from the corresponding *_FLAG_CONTRACTS table (as pm_copy does from COPY_FLAG_CONTRACTS since PR#545) instead of a hand-declared parallel table; contracts:check snapshot regenerated once and stays byte-stable across a no-op rebuild; a unit spec asserts no tool schema key exists without a backing flag-contract entry (drift becomes structurally impossible, not just snapshot-caught); MCP integration suites stay warning-clean"
